<LegalLayout
  active="privacy"
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="What Conan and conan.sh collect — and what they deliberately don't."
  updated="[DRAFT — set on publish]"
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how WhatMatters ("we", "us") handles
    information in connection with the Conan application and the conan.sh
    website. The short version: the app is built to keep your work on your
    machine, and the website collects only the minimum needed to run a waitlist
    and sell Premium.
  </p>

  <section id="overview">
    <h2>1. Overview</h2>
    <p>
      There are two surfaces to distinguish. The <strong>Conan app</strong> runs
      entirely on your Mac and sends us no telemetry. The <strong>conan.sh
      website</strong> collects limited data when you join the waitlist or
      purchase Premium. This policy covers both.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="collect">
    <h2>2. Data we collect (website)</h2>
    <h3>Waitlist</h3>
    <p>
      If you join the Windows/Linux waitlist, we collect the <strong>email
      address</strong> you submit, so we can notify you when those platforms are
      available. This is stored in our key-value store (Vercel/Upstash KV).
    </p>
    <h3>Purchases</h3>
    <p>
      When you buy Premium, payment is processed by <strong>Polar.sh</strong> as
      Merchant of Record. Polar collects the information needed to complete the
      sale (e.g. billing details); we receive purchase/entitlement confirmation
      but <strong>do not store your full payment-card details</strong>.
    </p>
    <span class="todo"
      >Enumerate every field actually collected at checkout and what Polar shares
      back to us (name, email, country, order id). Confirm whether we store the
      buyer's email for license delivery/support.</span
    >
  </section>

  <section id="app">
    <h2>3. The app: local-only</h2>
    <p>
      Conan reads Claude Code's local session data in <strong>~/.claude</strong>
      to visualize your activity. This processing happens on your device. Conan
      does not transmit your code, prompts, or session contents to us or any
      third party, and the app sends <strong>no analytics or telemetry</strong>.
    </p>
    <span class="todo"
      >Confirm there is genuinely zero outbound app traffic except (a) signed
      auto-update checks and (b) license validation, and describe exactly what
      each of those sends (e.g. version, license key — no personal data).</span
    >
  </section>

  <section id="use">
    <h2>4. How we use data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>to email you about Windows/Linux availability if you joined the waitlist;</li>
      <li>to fulfill and support your Premium purchase;</li>
      <li>to operate, secure, and improve the website.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information.</p>
    <span class="todo">Confirm we never use waitlist emails for unrelated marketing without consent.</span>
  </section>

  <section id="processors">
    <h2>5. Sharing & processors</h2>
    <p>We share data only with service providers that help us run the Service:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Polar.sh</strong> — payments / Merchant of Record;</li>
      <li><strong>Vercel</strong> — hosting and the KV store that holds waitlist emails;</li>
      <li><strong>[Email provider]</strong> — to send waitlist notifications.</li>
    </ul>
    <span class="todo"
